reviews.review: It should have been titled Star Wars: Flashing Lights. Also, the movie was filled with nonsensical, silly objectives, Deus ex machina solutions, and cheesy Disney lines. Not a Star Wars movie.

Absolutely phenomenal! Fantastic ending that perfectly ties in all three trilogies. I loved the fan service JJ provided. While not necessarily a deep or moving plot, and definitely could have benefited from a longer run time, this proves that JJ Abrams stuck the landing and satisfyingly wrapped up the Skywalker saga.
I loved everything about this movie.. it included Action, comedy & was so heartfelt!

i thought it was very badly written there were issues but everytime something went wrong there was a solution instantly. i thought that they brought characters back but gave no reasining. however the acting by Adam driver, Daisy Ridley was impressive and the cinematography and production design looked cool in certain scenes.

As one who has followed the epic Star Wars series over the years, I appreciate what J.J. Abrams did to wrap up this story. Though not as good as predecessors like The Empire Strikes Back or The Force Awakens, Rise of Skywalker was a totally fun thrill ride for one final run in the Star Wars universe. And to it's credit, I really enjoyed all the twists and turns this entry took to wrap up the story that began in 1977 with the classic original. A really fun movie and a satisfying conclusion. Especially for me.
